-- PRESS DIGEST - Bulgaria - June 23
-- 
-- Mon Jun 23, 2014 02:25AM EDT
-- None



SOFIA, June 23 (Reuters) - These are some of the main stories in Bulgarian newspapers on Monday. Reuters has not verified these stories and does not vouch for their accuracy.

-- The central bank and the government moved to nationalise Corporate Commercial Bank <6C9.BB> group by injecting capital and providing liquidity, so that the two banks restore operations on July 21. (24 Chasa, Trud, Presa, Capital Daily, Standart, Sega, Monitior) - Representatives of an Omani sovereign wealth fund, a shareholder in Corpbank with around 30 percent, will arrive in Sofia to hold talks with the central bank and the government and have expressed interest to provide support for the bank, sources familiar with the situation said. (24 Chasa, Standart) -- The torrential rains and floods have damaged one fifth of the area farmers put to wheat this year, which is likely to cut the grain crop by 25 percent from initially expected about 5 million tonnes, Farm Minister Dimitar Grekov said. (24 Chasa, Duma, Trud, Presa, Standart, Sega)